# Go SDK: Event context types

Define the event context types that are passed to callbacks, in `sdks/go/client/event.go`. These provide access to the database view and reducers within callback handlers.

## Types

```go
// EventContext is the base context available in all callbacks.
type EventContext struct {
    Identity     types.Identity
    ConnectionId types.ConnectionId
    Db           interface{}  // typed as RemoteTables in codegen
    Reducers     interface{}  // typed as RemoteReducers in codegen
    Event        Event
}

// ReducerEventContext adds reducer-specific info.
type ReducerEventContext struct {
    EventContext
    ReducerName string
    Status      ReducerStatus
    Timestamp   types.Timestamp
}

// SubscriptionEventContext for subscription lifecycle callbacks.
type SubscriptionEventContext struct {
    EventContext
    Db       interface{}
    Reducers interface{}
}

// ErrorContext for error callbacks.
type ErrorContext struct {
    Identity     *types.Identity  // may be nil if error before identity known
    ConnectionId *types.ConnectionId
    Err          error
}

// Event represents what triggered a callback.
type Event struct {
    Timestamp *types.Timestamp
    CallerIdentity *types.Identity
    CallerConnectionId *types.ConnectionId
    ReducerName string
    Status      ReducerStatus
    EnergyQuanta int64
}

type ReducerStatus int
const (
    ReducerStatusCommitted ReducerStatus = iota
    ReducerStatusFailed
    ReducerStatusOutOfEnergy
)
```

## Note on Generics

The codegen will produce typed versions of these contexts (e.g., `EventContext` with typed `Db` and `Reducers` fields). The base SDK provides the generic infrastructure, and codegen specializes it per module.

## Reference

- Rust SDK: `sdks/rust/src/event.rs`, `sdks/rust/src/db_context.rs`
- C#: `sdks/csharp/src/SpacetimeDB/Event.cs`

## Acceptance Criteria

- All context types defined
- Context types are usable in callback signatures
- ReducerStatus enum covers all server-reported statuses

# Go SDK: BSATN Writer (encoder)

Implement the BSATN binary encoder in `sdks/go/bsatn/writer.go`.

## BSATN Encoding Rules

All integers are **little-endian**. The Writer appends bytes to a growing buffer.

| Type | Encoding |
|------|----------|
| Bool | 1 byte: 0x00=false, 0x01=true |
| U8/I8 | 1 byte |
| U16/I16 | 2 bytes LE |
| U32/I32 | 4 bytes LE |
| U64/I64 | 8 bytes LE |
| U128/I128 | 16 bytes LE (low word first) |
| U256/I256 | 32 bytes LE |
| F32 | IEEE 754 bits written as U32 LE |
| F64 | IEEE 754 bits written as U64 LE |
| String | U32 LE byte length + UTF-8 bytes |
| Bytes | U32 LE length + raw bytes |
| Array | U32 LE element count + each element encoded sequentially |
| Product (struct) | Fields encoded in order, no separators |
| Sum (enum) | U8 tag (variant index) + variant payload |

## Implementation

```go
type Writer struct {
    buf []byte
}

func NewWriter() *Writer
func (w *Writer) Bytes() []byte
func (w *Writer) Reset()
func (w *Writer) Len() int

func (w *Writer) WriteBool(v bool)
func (w *Writer) WriteU8(v uint8)
func (w *Writer) WriteI8(v int8)
func (w *Writer) WriteU16(v uint16)
func (w *Writer) WriteI16(v int16)
func (w *Writer) WriteU32(v uint32)
func (w *Writer) WriteI32(v int32)
func (w *Writer) WriteU64(v uint64)
func (w *Writer) WriteI64(v int64)
func (w *Writer) WriteF32(v float32)
func (w *Writer) WriteF64(v float64)
func (w *Writer) WriteString(v string)
func (w *Writer) WriteBytes(v []byte)
func (w *Writer) WriteU128(lo, hi uint64)
func (w *Writer) WriteI128(lo, hi uint64)
func (w *Writer) WriteU256(v [32]byte)
func (w *Writer) WriteI256(v [32]byte)
func (w *Writer) WriteVariantTag(tag uint8)
func (w *Writer) WriteArrayLen(count uint32)
```

## Reference

- Rust: `crates/sats/src/bsatn/ser.rs`
- TypeScript: `crates/bindings-typescript/src/lib/binary_writer.ts`

## Acceptance Criteria

- All primitive write methods implemented
- Unit tests covering each type with known byte outputs
- Benchmark for bulk encoding (e.g., 10K struct products)

# Go SDK: BSATN Reader (decoder)

Implement the BSATN binary decoder in `sdks/go/bsatn/reader.go`.

## Implementation

```go
type Reader struct {
    data []byte
    pos  int
}

func NewReader(data []byte) *Reader
func (r *Reader) Remaining() int
func (r *Reader) IsEmpty() bool

func (r *Reader) ReadBool() (bool, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadU8() (uint8, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadI8() (int8, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadU16() (uint16, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadI16() (int16, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadU32() (uint32, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadI32() (int32, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadU64() (uint64, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadI64() (int64, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadF32() (float32, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadF64() (float64, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadString() (string, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadBytes() ([]byte, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadU128() (lo, hi uint64, err error)
func (r *Reader) ReadI128() (lo, hi uint64, err error)
func (r *Reader) ReadU256() ([32]byte, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadI256() ([32]byte, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadVariantTag() (uint8, error)
func (r *Reader) ReadArrayLen() (uint32, error)
```

All reads return errors on insufficient data. Decoding rules are symmetric to the Writer (STDB-2).

## Error Handling

Define error types:
- `ErrUnexpectedEOF` — not enough bytes remaining
- `ErrInvalidBool` — bool byte is not 0 or 1
- `ErrInvalidUtf8` — string bytes are not valid UTF-8

## Reference

- Rust: `crates/sats/src/bsatn/de.rs`
- TypeScript: `crates/bindings-typescript/src/lib/binary_reader.ts`

## Acceptance Criteria

- All primitive read methods implemented
- Round-trip tests: write value → read value → assert equal for all types
- Error path tests: truncated data, invalid bool, invalid UTF-8

# Go SDK: BSATN Serialize/Deserialize interfaces

Define Go interfaces for types that can be BSATN-encoded/decoded. These interfaces will be implemented by all generated types and special types.

## Implementation in `sdks/go/bsatn/interfaces.go`

```go
// Serializable can encode itself to BSATN.
type Serializable interface {
    WriteBsatn(w *Writer)
}

// Deserializable can decode itself from BSATN.
// Implemented as a static function pattern since Go interfaces can't have static methods.
// Codegen will produce: func ReadMyType(r *Reader) (MyType, error)

// For generic usage, define a type-parameterized codec:
type Codec[T any] interface {
    Write(w *Writer, v T)
    Read(r *Reader) (T, error)
}

// Helper functions for common patterns:
func Encode[T Serializable](v T) []byte
func Decode[T any](data []byte, read func(*Reader) (T, error)) (T, error)

// Option encoding (Sum type: tag 0 = None, tag 1 = Some)
func WriteOption[T any](w *Writer, v *T, writeElem func(*Writer, T))
func ReadOption[T any](r *Reader, readElem func(*Reader) (T, error)) (*T, error)

// Array/slice encoding
func WriteSlice[T any](w *Writer, s []T, writeElem func(*Writer, T))
func ReadSlice[T any](r *Reader, readElem func(*Reader) (T, error)) ([]T, error)

// Map encoding (as array of key-value products)
func WriteMap[K comparable, V any](w *Writer, m map[K]V, writeKey func(*Writer, K), writeVal func(*Writer, V))
func ReadMap[K comparable, V any](r *Reader, readKey func(*Reader) (K, error), readVal func(*Reader) (V, error)) (map[K]V, error)
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- Interfaces defined and documented
- Generic helper functions for Option, Slice, Map encoding/decoding
- `Encode`/`Decode` convenience functions work with round-trip tests
- Codegen can target these interfaces (design validated against codegen needs)

# Go SDK: AlgebraicType runtime representation

Implement the SATS AlgebraicType system in Go for runtime type introspection. This is needed for dynamic row parsing (e.g., BsatnRowList iteration where row schema is known at runtime).

## Types in `sdks/go/types/algebraic.go`

```go
type AlgebraicType interface {
    algebraicType() // sealed marker
}

type SumType struct {
    Variants []SumTypeVariant
}
type SumTypeVariant struct {
    Name *string
    Type AlgebraicType
}

type ProductType struct {
    Fields []ProductTypeField
}
type ProductTypeField struct {
    Name *string
    Type AlgebraicType
}

type ArrayType struct {
    ElemType AlgebraicType
}

// Primitive types as singleton constants
type BoolType struct{}
type StringType struct{}
type U8Type struct{}
type I8Type struct{}
type U16Type struct{}
// ... etc for all primitives

type RefType struct {
    Ref uint32
}
```

Also implement `Typespace`:
```go
type Typespace struct {
    Types []AlgebraicType
}
func (ts *Typespace) Resolve(ref uint32) AlgebraicType
```

## BSATN encode/decode for AlgebraicType itself

The AlgebraicType is itself BSATN-encodable (it's a Sum type in the wire protocol). Implement `WriteAlgebraicType` and `ReadAlgebraicType`.

## Reference

- Rust: `crates/sats/src/algebraic_type.rs`, `crates/sats/src/sum_type.rs`, `crates/sats/src/product_type.rs`
- TypeScript: `crates/bindings-typescript/src/lib/algebraic_type.ts`

## Acceptance Criteria

- All AlgebraicType variants representable
- Typespace with Ref resolution
- BSATN round-trip for AlgebraicType itself
